Changing Resolution: The “Lens” Idea

Your idea of a fighting lens or adjustable resolution is a useful metaphor.

We often move between levels:

Resolution	Tool	Example
very precise	mathematics	physics equations
mid-level	models/simulations	economic forecasts
human scale	language	instructions or stories

Each level captures different details. Tight constraints (like equations) reveal precise relations; looser grammars (like language) allow creativity and coordination.

